Bernalillo County Fire Department was live.
September 11 at 6:40 AM ¬∑

Never Forget!!!

BCFR Will Stand Guard For 343 Minutes!

The events that took place on September 11th, has forever changed the lives of every American. Join us tomorrow for our inaugural Fallen Heroes 9/11 Memorial as we broadcast the entire event live here on Facebook.

We are also offering a dedicated drive-through viewing lane. Bernalillo County residents are encouraged to stay in their vehicles and participate in a variety of ways: having a brief conversation with the BCFD Chaplin, offering an item to be part of the memorial, or taking pictures of the Guard and gear.

Event begins at 6:42 AM and will end at 12:30 PM @ 6840 2nd St. NW, Albuquerque, NM

Remember Bernalillo County, Stay Safe!

post_text:
An important message from Mr. Bryant:

Buenos Dias! Padres, estoy en el proceso de formar nuestro Equipo de Padres. Este equipo sera un comite en donde compartiremos diferentes ideas sobre como apoyar la escuela, como apoyar a nuestros estudiantes, y en ayudar a planificar varios eventos escolares. Tendremos una junta mensual. Si usted esta interesado/a en participar en este equipo, por favor dejeme saber. Gracias!

Good Morning! Parents, I am in the process of forming our Parent Advisory Team. This team will be a committee of volunteers in which we will brainstorm ideas on how to best support the school, how to best support our students, and will help with planning various school events. If you are interested in being part of this team, please let me know. Thank you!

Contact information: dbryant@lpelc.com

Good Morning,

ABA is preparing to issue additional devices beginning September 11, 2020. A shipment of 200 Chromebooks will be made available to any student actively enrolled in ABA online courses. A schedule for device pick up will be shared this week, as we will stagger pick up to avoid long lines.

Please complete the form below - you must complete one form for each ABA student residing in your household.

https://forms.gle/1puVc9PZfvxiLYkp8

Thank you for your patience during this challenging time. Our teachers continue to work hard to adapt to this model of teaching and learning. We would like to extend our appreciation to our parents, as you have done an exceptional job as our partners in learning. We hope the additional devices will help your online learning experience flow a little better.

Respectfully,

Mr. Jones

August 26 at 7:55 PM ¬∑

Did you know that you can DOUBLE your SNAP/EBT dollars with the Double Up Food Bucks program at the Rail Yards Market ABQ! Get locally grown produce from the market for half the price.

Its easy! Just bring your SNAP card to the info booth when you shop at the market or when you are picking up an order.

Thanks New Mexico Farmers' Markets for helping everyone in our State connect with local food!

August 15 at 11:31 AM ¬∑

It's happening TODAY, right here online on Facebook, our virtual Bosque Chile Festival!
Enjoy intoxicating poetry, instructive chef demos and lively musical performances from local acts.
We've also got a Chile Casas decorating contest and a online artisan market from local vendors with chile and inventive chile-related products.
Come back at 2 p.m. and enjoy the festival programming all day from the comfort of your home!
And come back on Sunday when we've got a whole new lineup! #BCF2020

We are celebrating #nationalwatermelondayüçâ with a watermelon volcano! First, hollow out a small watermelon. Then to beginning n the chemical reaction, add approximately 1/2 C of baking soda and make a well. Next, add a couple squirts of dish soap, then add red food coloring for dramatic effect! Finally, pour vinegar into the watermelon for it to continue to erupt üåã Mixing a base (baking soda) with an acid (vinegar) produces carbon dioxide causing the eruption. The dish soap adds the bubbles! #bakingsodascience #nuclearmuseum #trythisathome

üé•üçøü¶Å TONIGHT:

The movie, Lion King, has been rescheduled for Thursday, July 30. The movie will be shown at dusk at the parking lot of the Isleta Amphitheater at 5601 University Blvd, south of Rio Bravo.

Movies in the Park is free of charge and is on a first-come, first-served basis. Gates will open at 7 p.m. Cars will be parked in every other space and moviegoers are allowed to sit outside but only directly in front of their cars, in their assigned space. No one will be allowed to sit in spaces between cars. Social distancing will be observed and enforced by security.

Outside food and drink is permitted, but alcohol is not. Food trucks will be onsite. Attendees are required to wear a mask when venturing away from their vehicle or family for food or restrooms. Dogs are permitted onsite, but must be on a leash, and patrons must scoop their pet‚Äôs poop.

For more information, please call the Movies in the Park hotline at 505-314-0477 or visit bernco.gov/mitp.

Hi ABA Families,

Please help us by completing the 'Return to School' form below. We need to know by this Friday if your students will return for in-person instruction next year of if you will keep them home to learn online. A form is required for each student that attends ABA - please do not double up siblings.

Please know that we are making both options (online and in-person) available for our beloved families. We know this is a difficult time for all of you, and we want to do everything we can to help you get through this together, with the least continued impact on the children we all love.

https://forms.gle/tea5JapaYvNhTchw6

In Partnership,

Mr. Jones

post_text:
From NMPED, an update on where the last Phases of the Pandemic EBT benefits are currently at:

There was a small delay in the process of getting P-EBT out. The last phases of P-EBT will be issued and mailed out the week of July 6th. Please give some time for them to reach the households and they should reach the families and students by Mid July. The card will be mailed in the name of the eldest child that qualified for free and reduced lunch and participated in the National School Lunch Program along with any other sibling that also qualified on the same card and information to activate the card.

More information to come.

Hello ABA families, I want to let you know that our custodians are currently working hard in cleaning and sanitizing all classrooms for whenever our students return. At this moment we are asking for help with white semi gloss paint to do some touch ups on walls. If you're able to donate a gallon of white semi gloss paint please drop off at front office at our Unser location between the hours of 8-4pm Monday-Friday. Feel free to contact me at ddiaz@lpelc.com if you have any questions regarding this donation request. Thank you so much in advance for your help.

NASA - National Aeronautics and Space Administration was live.
May 30 at 9:00 AM ¬∑

Watch history unfold on Saturday, May 30, as NASA and SpaceX launch astronauts Robert Behnken and Douglas Hurley to the International Space Station. This mission marks the first time since the retirement of the space shuttle in 2011 that humans will fly to the space station from U.S. soil. The first launch attempt on May 27 was scrubbed due to weather.

Set a reminder to tune for joint NASA/SpaceX coverage starting at 11 a.m. EDT, with liftoff currently targeted for 3:22 p.m. EDT. üöÄ

An important message from Mr. Jones:

Hi Parents:

We hope our ABA families are doing well. As we move closer to the re-opening of the state, we send well wishes and share our sentiment of hope with each of you. The entire staff misses seeing the faces and hearing the voices of our students and families. Please know that we are already preparing for next year and are committed to working as hard as possible to see to it that our entire school community can return to what we have come to know as normal; with students growing socially and academically.

Please take five minutes to help us plan for next year by completing the following NEEDS ASSESSMENT SURVEY:

https://forms.gle/Kw8oQdNtNJpyvhmn7

Thank you for your partnership!

Mr. Jones

The Albuquerque Bilingual Academy is searching for a Middle School Science Teacher, can you help us spread the word?

SY20-21 FT Middle School Science Teacher

Albuquerque Bilingual Academy

Qualifications: Valid Elementary K-8 OR Middle Level license with Science endorsement; excellent classroom/student management experience; experience working with adolescent learners; experience analyzing and utilizing data to make instructional decisions; ability to differentiate for diverse learners with various levels of Spanish language proficiency; experience working under pressure in a high-paced environment; experience developing common formative assessments; proven ability to work as a member of a team, and actively participating in collaboration and professional development experiences; Open until filled.

Happy ‚Äúwhat would have been‚Äù Run for the Zoo day! In commemoration of today, we‚Äôre excited to announce the first-ever VIRTUAL Run for the Zoo, May 17-24!

While we can‚Äôt run together in person, we can still support the ABQ BioPark ‚ÄúSix Feet Apart. Miles Together.‚Äù

Registration opens on Wednesday, May 6, and costs just $10 for all ages and race distances! Choose from a half marathon, 10K, 5K or 1 Mile ‚Äúyour way‚Äù. Upgrade your registration to include the official Virtual Run for the Zoo t-shirt, and just like the original event, 100% of all proceeds directly support your BioPark! https://bit.ly/virtualrunforthezoo
